(64, 6, 'MB', 'Did you drink shortly before getting arrested?', 'Rising', 14, 'Yes,Rising2,rising bac defense|No,,', '', 0),
(65, 6, 'EX', '<b>Rising BAC Defense</b><br/><br/>You may have a &quot;Rising BAC Defense.&quot; What matters in a DUI/DWI case is your BAC at the time of driving&#44; not your BAC at the police station. To figure this out&#44; prosecutors will try to estimate your driving BAC. Most of the time they will estimate a BAC higher than the test results because they assume that your body was burning off alcohol between the time of arrest and testing. However&#44; this assumption is false if you had a drink shortly before being arrested and/or tested&#44; because your body was still absorbing that drink. This is called the &quot;Rising BAC defense&quot; and it might be used to help your case.	', 'Rising2', 15, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
(66, 6, 'EX', '<b>High BAC</b><br/><br/>If you have a BAC of 0.15% or higher&#44; a DWI may be charged as a class A misdemeanor for the first offense. A class A misdemeanor imposes a jail sentence up to 1 year and a fine up to $4000. ', 'High BAC', 16, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
