(2510, 75, 'EX', '<b>Benefit</b><br/><br/>An internship should be  designed as an extension of the worker&#39;s educational experience and should be for the benefit of the worker&#44; not your company. The worker should not be engaged in the regular and routine work of your company&#39;s operations that benefit the company. If the purpose of the internship is to derive benefit to your company&#44; the worker is probably not an intern. ', 'Benefit', 2, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
(2511, 75, 'EX', '<b>Regular Employees</b><br/><br/>An intern can not displace regular employees. If the worker is doing the same work a paid employee would be doing within your company&#44; then the worker is probably not an intern. The fact that a company would pay for someone to do the work is evidence that the work is important. Workers should get paid for work that is important to a company&#39;s operations. ', 'Same', 6, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
(2512, 75, 'EX', '<b>Supervision</b><br/><br/>Interns usually work under close supervision. If a worker is under the same level of supervision as a regular employee&#44; the worker is probably not an intern. Close supervision is necessary for interns because the your main duty is to provide the intern with an opportunity to learn certain functions within the employment setting. ', 'Supervision', 5, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
(2513, 75, 'EX', '<b>Immediate Benefit</b><br/><br/>Your company cannot receive an immediate benefit from the worker in order to classify that person as an intern. In fact&#44; sometimes your operations may be impeded by having the worker around. This is because an internship is for the benefit of the worker and not the company. ', 'Immediate', 8, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
(2514, 75, 'EX', '<b>Job</b><br/><br/>The duration of the internship period must be fixed in the beginning. At the end of the internship period&#44; an intern is not guaranteed a job. It may be a possibility&#44; but not a guarantee. You can&#39;t use the period as a trial and give the expectation that the worker will be hired at the end. ', 'Job', 10, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
(2515, 75, 'EX', '<b>Understanding</b><br/><br/>It should be made clear that the worker is not to be paid (or be paid below minimum wage of a stipend) from the beginning of the internship. A lack of this understanding might be evidence that the worker is not an intern. ', 'Understand', 12, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
(2516, 75, 'EX', '<b>Educational</b><br/><br/>The type of training an intern receives should be similar to training that would be given in an educational environment. This is because an internship should be an extension of a worker&#39;s educational experience. ', 'Educational', 14, 'Continue,,,', '', 0),
